Several people were killed in a fiery car crash between Grobersdal and Marble Hall in the early hours of Friday morning, Limpopo police said. It is alleged that a vehicle lost control and hit a marula tree on the edge of the road and caught fire with the occupant/s inside along the R33 road between Groblersdal and Marble Hall. The cause of this accident is still unknown , said police spokesperson Lieutenant-Colonel Moatshe Ngoepe. He said the number of occupants and their identities was still unknown. The burnt car is a Hyundai i20, and anyone who could assist in the identification of the deceased, may go to Groblersdal Police Station. Police investigations are still continuing. Police have opened a case of culpable homicide. -African News Agency (ANA). For more news your way, follow The Citizen on Facebook and Twitter. For more news your way, follow The Citizen on Facebook and Twitter. For more news your way, follow The Citizen on Facebook and Twitter.